args: What do you mean, Lathna's your enemy?
He and I are of the same belief in the\nmatter of protecting the Great Ones.
But he is an agent of the Outer Gods.\nHe longs for chaos above all—exists\nonly to instill madness in all that is.
In other words, his very existence is a\nthorn in my side. Thus, I thought to use\nyou to humiliate him.
What do I have to do with any of this?
Until this moment, he has never invited\na dreamer into this world. It seems he\nhas quite the attachment to you.
I want nothing more than to see him rage\nover having his favorite toy stolen away.
I don't understand most of what you're\nsaying...
But Lathna is just a normal girl!\nThe same as me.
So please don't hurt her.\nShe's too important to me!
So this is what you humans call\n＂friendship.＂ What say YOU, hm?
Let me hear your answer,\nN Y A R L A T H O T E P.
We are the crawling chaos. We are the\nshadow that writhes in the darkness. We\nare the Other who stands at your back.
Lathna! When did you get here?!
Lord of the Great Abyss. He who invites\nUs to such wicked festivities. A rancid\neffluvium hangs ever about you.

I saw fit to greet you with matching
dignity. The rotting stench of the
caterpillars is a most fitting shroud
for you and your blackened entrails.

Though we oppose one another, we are
guardians who must cooperate all the
same. By what foolish scheme do you
violate our accord?
I ought to ask you the same thing. It seems\nyou have been visiting the Dreamlands\noften of late. What are you plotting?

We are the Black and White. The Criminal
and the Innocent. It has been centuries
since We last crossed the threshold into
these lands.
So you claim ignorance. Or perhaps... No,\nit is of no matter. Instead, I must ask you.
What thoughts did you have when that girl\nwas taken from you? What emotions did\nyou harbor that brought you here?

Your desire will not be granted.
We came only to depose a despot.
Humans are sacrificial pawns.
We take no interest in them.
Oh, so you would attack me like a common\ndog? How unlike you to forego strategy.
Allow me to postulate. The will that\nbrought you here was not your own,\nNyarlathotep.
One of you...the girl named Lathna...spoke\nto the depths of your consciousness and\nbegged you to save her friend.

You extol chaos with your thousand forms.
Yet I believe these selves, each with their
own identity, are fraying the fabric of your
tenuous integrity.

With every face is born more connections,
each creating something new you must
protect. I simply cannot wait to see you at
their mercy—a thrall to your sentiments!
You weave baseless assumptions.\nWe shall not entertain this puerile line\nof questioning any longer.
Oh, have I hit a nerve? What bliss!\nHow I love to hear you suffer!
This alone makes tonight a most fruitful\nharvest. I shan't play any longer.

Guardians of the Great Ones we may be,
yet We would abstain from your company.
Begone and remain in the depths of the
abyss forevermore, away from Us always.
You... You ARE Lathna, aren't you?
Are you here to save me?
...Humans are sacrificial pawns.\nWe take no interest in them.
Our ambition shall not be shackled by an\ninferior existence. If you think to hinder\nUs, then We shall send you to your grave.
Offering. Oblation.\nWe ask you before you sink into oblivion.\nWhy did you come to this land of dreams?
Hee hee! Now we match!\nLet's put our hair up the same way too.
We are Chaos. Messenger of the One.\nYou, a fool who wallows in mud.\nWe are... We...are...
Pia? No...! NO! Did I do this?!
Looks like I made it just in time.
Where...am I? Is this my room?
Rise and shine, Lathna.\nIt's time for breakfast.
You still sawin' logs over there, kiddo?

You left in the middle of the festival,
came back here, and went straight to bed.
Sleeping in your yukata like that isn't
very ladylike, you know.
She's probably already sittin' down to eat.\nWell? Don't keep the girl waiting.\nGet dressed and head straight on over.
What are you doing, Pia?\nC'mon, let's sit down.
